\begin_layout AbstractEN
Typesetting is a long-standing notorious troublesome for the scientific
 researchers.
 The noticeable drawback in LaTeX typesetting is that control characters
 and text characters appear in the same time, likely breaking user to input
 text.
 In view of this, we propose a novel combination of LyX + XeLaTeX + LaTeX
 in editing paper.
 In this way, LaTeX learnes from Lyx's strong points to offset its weakness,
 with advantages of both MS Word and TeX typesetting.
 In additional XeLaTeX engine, based on Uincode, not only improves compatibility
 but also makes it more convenient to be used.
 This work also presents a set of LaTeX/LyX templates of South China University
 of Technology doctoral thesis, in order to verify the feasibility of the
 combination.
\end_layout

